"{\"uid\": \"canberratimes.com.au-story-8752831-aussie-b-girl-raygun-to-apologises-after-olympic-backlash\", \"text\": \"Your digital subscription includes access to content from all our websites in your region.\\r Access unlimited news content and The Canberra Times app. Premium subscribers also enjoy interactive puzzles and access to the digital version of our print edition - Today's Paper.  Australian b-girlRachael 'Raygun' Gunnhas apologised for her performance at the Olympics in an emotional interview.  Loginor signup to continue reading  Ms Gunn, a Macquarie University lecturer, receivedharsh criticism from online commentersafter her performance on August 10.  Her odd moves, such as the kangaroo, were widely mocked and made her a viral sensation.  In a preview of her interview on Channel 10'sThe ProjectMs Gunn said she was \\\"very sorry\\\" for the backlash the dance community experienced after her performance.  \\\"But I cannot control how people react,\\\" she said.  Ms Gunn said she was \\\"sad\\\" to hearcriticism of her performanceand felt a \\\"state of panic\\\" after reporters chased her down streets.  Asked whether she \\\"genuinely\\\" thought she was the best female break dancer in Australia, she was unapologetic.  \\\"I think my record speaks to that,\\\" Ms Gunn said.  The full interview with Waleed Aly is set air on Channel 10'sThe Projectfrom 6.30pm on September 4.  Carla Mascarenhas is the NSW correspondent covering breaking news, state politics and investigations. She is based in Sydney. Contact her on carla.mascarenhas@austcommunitymedia.com.au  Carla Mascarenhas is the NSW correspondent covering breaking news, state politics and investigations. She is based in Sydney. Contact her on carla.mascarenhas@austcommunitymedia.com.au  Daily  Today's top stories curated by our news team. Also includes evening update.  As it happens  Do not miss updates on news about the Public Service.  Weekdays  Grab a quick bite of today's latest news from around 